Some Notes on a curious habit of male
humble bees were sent to Prof. Hermann Müller, of
Lippstadt, who had permission from Mr. Darwin to make
what use he pleased of them. After Müller’s death the
Notes were given by his son to Dr. E. Krause, who
published them under the title, “Ueber die Wege der
HummelMännchen” in his book, ‘Gesammelte kleinere
Schriften von Charles Darwin’
(1887).
