Schlesische Gesellschaft für
Vaterländische Cultur (Breslau). Hon. Member,
1878.

Cæsarea Leopoldino-Carolina Academia
Naturæ Curiosorum (Dresden).
1857. (The diploma contains the words “accipe … ex
antiqua nostra consuetudine cognomen Forster.” It was
formerly the custom in the

Cæsarea Leopoldino-Carolina Academia
, that
each new member should receive as a ‘cognomen,’ a name
celebrated in that branch of science to which he
belonged. Thus a physician might be christened
Boerhaave, or an astronomer, Kepler. My father seems to
have been named after the traveller John Reinhold
Forster.)

